title: For Sale:  RWS Diana 48 .177 air rifle, Scope Ready, German Made
postcontent:
I'm selling my RWS Diana 48 because I haven't used it in a few years. The air rifle has proven both powerful and accurate...a real pleasure to shoot with. With a scope, I was able to routinely place 5 pellets in a bit over an inch at 50yds. Cans and Varmints beware!

With light pellets, the rifle will frequently emit the tell tale crack as the pellet crosses the sound barrier (~1100fps). However the robust spring piston much prefers heavier 10.5 gr pellets. 

Included with the rifle is an adjustable scope mount, necessary for proper sighting on most air rifles. I have a Sims Limb Saver butt pad on the rifle to give it a bit longer length of pull. 

I will consider trading locally a Henry Lever action 22lr. 

As this is an air rifle and thus does not require FFL to transfer out of state,  I'm willing to ship for an additional $25. Payment will need to be made via cashier's check or money order and shipment will wait till payment clears my account. Please know your local laws before contacting me. 

Please feel free to contact me with any more questions or if you desire more pictures.

title: For Sale:  1866 Uberti Yellowboy Sport Rifle
postcontent:
Own a piece of American History.  This design originated from Henry rifles but it had flaws. In 1866, Oliver Winchester took over the another company and named it Winchester Repeating Arms Co. and that same year he made improvements on this Henry Rifle design and introduced it as the Yellowboy. 

This 1866 Uberti Yellowboy Sport Rifle, is a clone of one of the most popular rifle’s of the late 1800’s, which was carried by Chief Sitting Bull, the armies of Benito Juarez and the Turkish armies of the time.  This .45 caliber has a 24.25” octagon barrel and holds 13+1 rounds.  It has a brass frame, brass buttplate, a case hardened lever, a brass fore-end nose cap and a Grade A walnut stock.  This is a new gun and it has never been fired.
